d with a specific path prefix can be bypassed using URL-encoded characters (e.g., \"/%61dmin\" instead of \"/admin\"). While the middleware engine fails to match the encoded path and skips execution, the underlying Fastify router correctly decodes the path and matches the route handler, allowing attackers to access protected endpoints without the middleware constraints. Version 9.1.0 fixes the issue.\n\n<p>Publish Date: 2026-01-19\n<p>URL: <a href=https://www.mend.io/vulnerability-database/CVE-2026-22031>CVE-2026-22031</a></p>\n</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n###  CVSS 3 Score Details (<b>8.4</b>)\n<p>\n\nBase Score Metrics:\n- Exploitability Metrics:\n  - Attack Vector: Network\n  - Attack Complexity: High\n  - Privileges Required: Low\n  - User Interaction: None\n  - Scope: Changed\n- Impact Metrics:\n  - Confidentiality Impact: High\n  - Integrity Impact: High\n  - Availability Impact: Low\n</p>\nFor more information on CVSS3 Scores, click <a href=\"https://www.first.org/cvss/calculator/3.0\">here</a>.\n</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n###  Suggested Fix\n<p>\n\n<p>Type: Upgrade version</p>\n<p>Release Date: 2026-01-19</p>\n<p>Fix Resolution: @⁠fastify/middie - 9.1.0,https://github.com/fastify/middie.git - v9.1.0</p>\n\n</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n\nStep up your Open Source Security Game with Mend [here](https://www.whitesourcesoftware.com/full_solution_bolt_github)\n</details><details>\n\n<summary><img src='https://whitesource-resources.whitesourcesoftware.com/high_vul.png?' width=19 height=20> CVE-2026-4800</summary>\n\n\n###  Vulnerable Library - <b>lodash-4.17.21.tgz</b>\n\n<p>Lodash modular utilities.</p>\n<p>Library home page: <a href=\"https://registry.npmjs.org/lodash/-/lodash-4.17.21.tgz\">https://registry.npmjs.org/lodash/-/lodash-4.17.21.tgz</a></p>\n<p>Path to dependency file: /package.json</p>\n<p>Path to vulnerable library: /package.json</p>\n<p>\n\nDependency Hierarchy:\n  - @⁠career-compass/api-0.0.1.tgz (Root Library)\n    - swagger-7.3.0.tgz\n      - :x: **lodash-4.17.21.tgz** (Vu