//api.github.com/repos/ducktors/turborepo-remote-cache/issues/758/events","html_url":"https://github.com/ducktors/turborepo-remote-cache/issues/758","id":4398166963,"node_id":"I_kwDOGjFZDc8AAAABBiazsw","number":758,"title":"BODY_LIMIT env silently ignored in image 2.8.4 — all PUT > 1MB rejected (fastify 5.8.5 wiring regression?)","user":{"login":"bigtrader91","id":88607278,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg4NjA3Mjc4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/88607278?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigtrader91","html_url":"https://github.com/bigtrader91","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigtrader91/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigtrader91/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigtrader91/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigtrader91/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigtrader91/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigtrader91/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigtrader91/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigtrader91/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigtrader91/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":4536636688,"node_id":"LA_kwDOGjFZDc8AAAABDmeVEA","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ducktors/turborepo-remote-cache/labels/released","name":"released","color":"ededed","default":false,"description":null}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-05-07T10:52:10Z","updated_at":"2026-05-23T09:16:52Z","closed_at":"2026-05-23T09:15:58Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":{"id":17765144,"node_id":"IT_kwDOBsUxy84BDxMY","name":"Bug","description":"An unexpected problem or behavior","color":"red","created_at":"2024-02-14T06:32:12Z","updated_at":"2024-07-26T14:43:06Z","is_enabled":true},"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## 🐛 Bug Report\n\n`BODY_LIMIT` env variable reaches the running process correctly but is **silently not applied** to the underlying fastify instance, so the default 1MB limit is enforced regardless of the env value. All PUTs with payload > 1MB return `FST_ERR_CTP_BODY_TOO_LARGE` (413/500), making the cache effectively unusable for any non-trivial monorepo artifact.\n\nThis appears related to but distinct from #250 (which added the `BODY_LIMIT` option) and #366 (default raised to 50MB via #384). In the current `:latest` image the env value is read but not wired into the fastify constructor's `bodyLimit` option.\n\n## To Reproduce\n\n**Environment:**\n- Image: `ducktors/turborepo-remote-cache:latest` (resolved digest at test time = `2.8.4`)\n- Fastify version (per image lockfile): `5.8.5`\n- Storage: `STORAGE_PROVIDER=local`, docker volume\n- Host: Docker on Linux, container bound `127.0.0.1:13030 → 3000`\n- Token: random 32-byte hex via `TURBO_TOKEN`\n- Tested 2026-05-04\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. Run the image with an explicit large `BODY_LIMIT`:\n\n   ```bash\n   docker run -d \\\n     --name turbo-cache \\\n     -p 127.0.0.1:13030:3000 \\\n     -v turbo-cache-data:/data \\\n     -e STORAGE_PROVIDER=local -e STORAGE_PATH=/data \\\n     -e TURBO_TOKEN=\"<random>\" \\\n     -e BODY_LIMIT=524288000 \\\n     ducktors/turborepo-remote-cache:latest\n   ```\n\n2. Verify env reaches the process inside the container:\n\n   ```bash\n   docker exec turbo-cache node -e 'console.log(process.env.BODY_LIMIT)'\n   # → 524288000\n   docker exec turbo-cache node -e \"import('./dist/env.js').then(m => console.log(m.env.get().BODY_LIMIT))\"\n   # → 524288000  (number coerce works)\n   ```\n\n3. Issue a turbo cache PUT for an artifact > 1MB (e.g. a Next.js standalone build, ~43MB in our case) via `turbo run build` against `TURBO_API=http://127.0.0.1:13030`.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nPUT succeeds because `BODY_LIMIT=524288000` (500 MB) is well above the artifact size.\n\n## Actual behavior\n\n```\n{\n  \\\"severity\\\":\\\"ERROR\\\",\n  \\\"level\\\":50,\n  \\\"code\\\":\\\"FST_ERR_CTP_BODY_TOO_LARGE\\\",\n  \\\"message\\\":\\\"Request body is too large\\\",\n  \\\"statusCode\\\":413,\n  \\\"stack\\\":\\\"FastifyError: Request body is too large\n    at rawBody (.../fastify@5.8.5/lib/contentTypeParser.js:.../...)\n    at ContentTypeParser.run ...\\\"\n}\n```\n\nClient side observes `WARNING failed to contact remote cache: ... HTTP status client error (413 Payload Too Large)`. Behavior is identical for any payload > 1 MB regardless of `BODY_LIMIT` value (tested 50 MB, 500 MB, 1000 MB).\n\nThis implies fastify is being constructed with the **default** 1MB `bodyLimit` (fastify 5.x default), not the env-provided value — i.e. the wiring between `env.get().BODY_LIMIT` and `fastify({ bodyLimit })` is no longer connected, or is connected before the option is read.\n\n## Diagnosis hypothesis\n\nIn fastify 5.x the `bodyLimit` option must be passed at instance construction (it cannot be set via plugin after instantiation). If the `app = fastify({...})` call in `dist/app.js` (or wherever the server is bootstrapped) reads from a stale-cached env or hard-codes `bodyLimit`, the runtime value would be ignored. The default 1MB matches fastify 5's default, suggesting `bodyLimit` is simply omitted from the constructor options.\n\nWorkaround paths attempted:\n- Setting `BODY_LIMIT` to various values (50M, 500M, 1G) — no change.\n- Exporting via various env mechanisms (docker `-e`, `--env-file`, compose `environment:`) — env reaches process per step 2 above.\n\n## Your Environment\n\n- Container image: `ducktors/turborepo-remote-cache:latest` (sha resolves to 2.8.4 at time of test)\n- Fastify (in image): `5.8.5`\n- Node: as bundled in image\n- Host docker: Linux x86_64\n- Turbo CLI: `2.9.5`\n\n## Reference / context\n\n- Downstream tracking issue: https://github.com/nodaji-lab/starter-kit/issues/180\n- Affects all monorepos with standalone build artifacts > 1MB (Next.js, Nx, etc.)\n- Closed PR #384 raised default to 50MB but the symptom suggests the env-wiring path itself is broken in the current image — even the 50MB default does not appear to take effect (unverified — but artifacts up to 43MB are rejected which is *below* 50MB, ruling out \\\"just need higher default\\\" as the only fix)\n\nIf a maintainer can confirm the constructor wiring or a published image rebuild is planned, downstream consumers can rest. Happy to test patches against a tagged image if useful.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ducktors/turborepo-remote-cache/issues/758/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ducktors/turborepo-remote-cache/issues/758/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fastify/otel/issues/152","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fastify/otel","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fastify/otel/issues/152/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fastify/otel/issues/152/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fastify/otel/issues/152/events","html_url":"https://github.com/fastify/otel/issues/152","id":4386746215,"node_id":"I_kwDONVik4M8AAAABBXhvZw","number":152,"title":"Server request span kind is set to `SpanKind.INTERNAL`","user":{"login":"BraedonLeonard","id":10601513,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwNjAxNTEz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10601513?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/BraedonLeonard","html_url":"https://github.com/BraedonLeonard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BraedonLeonard/followers","following_url"