ll,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## CVE\n- **ID:** CVE-2026-6321\n- **Package:** `fast-uri@3.1.0` → fix at `fast-uri@3.1.1`\n- **Severity:** HIGH (EPSS: 0.00036)\n- **Vulnerability class:** CWE-22 — Path Traversal via percent-encoded dot segments\n- **GHSA:** GHSA-q3j6-qgpj-74h6\n- **Transitivity:** transitive (parents in CE root: `fastify@5.8.5` → `@fastify/ajv-compiler` / `fast-json-stringify` → `fast-uri`, also `@fastify/swagger` → `json-schema-resolver` → `fast-uri`, and `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` → `ajv@8.20.0` → `fast-uri`; parent in mcp-docs: `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk@1.27.1` → `ajv@8.18.0` → `fast-uri`)\n\n## Locations\n- `package-lock.json:12563` (and dedup entries at lines 1560, 9352, 12529, 14455)\n- `mcp-docs/package-lock.json:2035` (request range at `mcp-docs/package-lock.json:1455`)\n\n## Summary\n`fast-uri` v3.1.0 and earlier decode percent-encoded path separators (`%2F`) and dot segments (`%2E`) before applying dot-segment removal in `normalize()` and `equal()`. Encoded path data behaves like real `/` and `..`, so distinct URIs collapse onto the same normalized path (e.g. `http://example.com/public/%2e%2e/admin` normalizes to `http://example.com/admin`). Applications that normalize or compare attacker-controlled URLs to enforce path-based policy can be bypassed.\n\n## Reachability\n**Reachability assessment: unlikely.** Compendiq does not import `fast-uri` directly (`grep -rn \"fast-uri\" backend/src` returns nothing). The library is reached only through Fastify's internal request pipeline (URL parsing for routing) and Ajv's JSON Schema `format: uri` validators used by `@fastify/swagger` and `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk`. We do not call `normalize()` or `equal()` on user-supplied URLs to make trust decisions; route matching happens against fixed route templates and Zod schemas (`@compendiq/contracts`) validate request bodies. The vulnerability could in principle bite us if a Zod-or-Ajv-validated `format: uri` field is later used as an allowlist key — not a pattern present today, but worth patching defensively. mcp-docs has its own SSRF/domain-filter guard (`mcp-docs/src/security/ssrf-guard.ts`) that does not use `fast-uri`.\n\n## Proposed remediation\nAdd a root `overrides` entry so both workspaces and the nested mcp-docs lockfile pick up the patched version. CE root `package.json` already has an `overrides` block — extend it.\n\n```json\n\"overrides\": {\n  \"fast-uri\": \"^3.1.2\"\n}\n```\n\nNote: pinning to `^3.1.2` (rather than `^3.1.1`) also fixes the related CVE-2026-6322 in a single bump — see companion issue. The mcp-docs workspace has its own lockfile and may need a separate `overrides` entry inside `mcp-docs/package.json` or a fresh `npm install` from the mcp-docs directory.\n\n## Related CVEs\n- CVE-2026-6322 (fast-uri host confusion, fix at 3.1.2) — both can be remediated by a single bump to `fast-uri@^3.1.2`. File companion issue.\n\n## References\n- GHSA: https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-q3j6-qgpj-74h6\n- Advisory: https://github.com/fastify/fast-uri/security/advisories/GHSA-q3j6-qgpj-74h6\n- NVD: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-6321\n\n---\n_Filed by automated Semgrep triage. Source: Semgrep cloud SCA scan._","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/637/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/637/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fastify/fastify-http-proxy/issues/461","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fastify/fastify-http-proxy","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fastify/fastify-http-proxy/issues/461/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://a