github.com/users/laboef1900/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":10547636189,"node_id":"LA_kwDORyqgoc8AAAACdLAn3Q","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/labels/priority:high","name":"priority:high","color":"D93F0B","default":false,"description":"Should fix soon"},{"id":10595087375,"node_id":"LA_kwDORyqgoc8AAAACd4Q0Dw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/labels/security","name":"security","color":"B60205","default":false,"description":"Security-related issues"},{"id":10627238917,"node_id":"LA_kwDORyqgoc8AAAACeW7MBQ","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/labels/dependencies","name":"dependencies","color":"0366d6","default":false,"description":"Pull requests that update a dependency file"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-14T09:04:51Z","updated_at":"2026-05-14T16:59:39Z","closed_at":"2026-05-14T16:59:39Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## CVE\n- **ID:** CVE-2026-6322\n- **Package:** `fast-uri@3.1.0` (and 3.1.1) → fix at `fast-uri@3.1.2`\n- **Severity:** HIGH (EPSS: 0.00035)\n- **Vulnerability class:** Host confusion / URL parsing interpretation conflict (CWE-436)\n- **GHSA:** GHSA-v39h-62p7-jpjc\n- **Transitivity:** transitive (parents in CE root: `fastify@5.8.5` → `@fastify/ajv-compiler` / `fast-json-stringify` → `fast-uri`; `@fastify/swagger` → `json-schema-resolver` → `fast-uri`; `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` → `ajv@8.20.0` → `fast-uri`; parent in mcp-docs: `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk@1.27.1` → `ajv@8.18.0` → `fast-uri`)\n\n## Locations\n- `package-lock.json:12563` (dedup entries at 1560, 9352, 12529, 14455)\n- `mcp-docs/package-lock.json:2035` (request range at `mcp-docs/package-lock.json:1455`)\n\n## Summary\n`fast-uri` v3.1.1 and earlier decode percent-encoded authority delimiters (`%40` → `@`, `%3A` → `:`) inside the host component and serialize them back as raw characters. This changes the URI structure: `http://trusted.com%40evil.com/` normalizes to `http://trusted.com@evil.com/`, which reparses as host `evil.com` with userinfo `trusted.com`. Applications that normalize untrusted URLs before host allowlist checks, redirect validation, or outbound request routing can be steered to a different authority than the original URL appeared to contain.\n\n## Reachability\n**Reachability assessment: unlikely (but defensive-patch worthwhile).** Compendiq does not call `fast-uri` directly. The closest reachable surface is mcp-docs' outbound URL handling (`mcp-docs/src/security/ssrf-guard.ts`, `mcp-docs/src/security/domain-filter.ts`), where the MCP server applies its own host allowlist before fetching arbitrary URLs on behalf of the LLM — that path uses Node's WHATWG `URL`, not `fast-uri`, so the bug doesn't traverse our trust boundary today. However, any future code that relies on a `format: uri` Ajv validator to confirm a host before performing an outbound action would inherit this confusion bug. Fastify's request URL parsing uses fast-uri internally but applies normalization for routing, not for trust decisions.\n\n## Proposed remediation\nSame fix as the companion CVE — bump to `3.1.2` (which supersedes 3.1.1 and remediates both CVEs in one step).\n\n```json\n\"overrides\": {\n  \"fast-uri\": \"^3.1.2\"\n}\n```\n\nThe mcp-docs workspace has its own lockfile; either add an `overrides` entry to `mcp-docs/package.json` or run `npm install` from `mcp-docs/` after the parent override lands.\n\n## Related CVEs\n- CVE-2026-6321 (fast-uri path traversal, fix at 3.1.1) — companion issue #637. A single bump to `^3.1.2` fixes both.\n\n## References\n- GHSA: https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-v39h-62p7-jpjc\n- Advisory: https://github.com/fastify/fast-uri/security/advisories/GHSA-v39h-62p7-jpjc\n- NVD: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-6322\n\n---\n_Filed by automated Semgrep triage. Source: Semgrep cloud SCA scan._","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/639/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/639/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0}],"search_type":"lexical"}